# CHORD BASICS
# ============
# A triad (basic chord) has three notes:
#   Root  = the fundamental note (gives the chord its name)
#   Third = 3 or 4 semitones above root (major or minor)
#   Fifth = 7 semitones above root (perfect fifth)
#
# Examples in C major:
#   C major  = C4 + E4 + G4  (root, major third, fifth)
#   F major  = F3 + A3 + C4  (root, major third, fifth)
#   G major  = G3 + B3 + D4  (root, major third, fifth)
#   A minor  = A3 + C4 + E4  (root, minor third, fifth)
#   D minor  = D3 + F3 + A3  (root, minor third, fifth)

# SIMULTANEOUS TIMING [@]
# =======================
# The [@] marker means "at the same time as the previous event"
# This lets us play chord notes together:
